# Trivy ignore list — acknowledged risks documented.
# Format: one CVE per line; optional `expiration: YYYY-MM-DD` comment.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lefthook (devDependency) Go stdlib CVEs — bundled binary at
# node_modules/.pnpm/lefthook-linux-x64@2.1.6/.../bin/lefthook
#
# Why ignored: lefthook is a git-hook runner used by developers locally and
# in the dev compose `workspace` stage only. It is NOT installed in any
# production runtime image (api/worker/scheduler/migration all use
# `pnpm install --prod` which omits devDependencies). The CVEs cannot be
# patched until upstream lefthook publishes a release built against
# Go >= 1.26.3. Latest stable on npm is 2.1.6 as of 2026-05-17.
#
# Re-evaluate when lefthook 2.2+ ships. Track:
#   https://github.com/evilmartians/lefthook/releases
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
